    "kernel": "5.15.0-52-generic",
    "notes": "Tried as many solutions as I could find here and on other places. Primary problem appears to be EA App.\n1. Replacing EAappinstaller.exe with re-named OriginThinSetup.exe causes launch to freeze at setting up Origin.\n2. Switching between multiple Proton versions (experimental to 6.3-8) does nothing\n3. Manually installed EA App through Lutris, however game simply gets error message \"An error on our end caused your launch to fail. Try again a little later.\"\n\nThankfully I bought it on sale so its a minor loss, I'm going to keep it in case a genuine fix is found. I don't blame anyone except EA for this honestly, Origin was trash from the get-go save for the occasional free game (that eventually went away). So I think its inevitable that EA App would also be trash. Why game publishers insist on layering launchers in front of their games is beyond me especially since I bought the game from Steam.",
